result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (2nd) and Operating w/ PAC (2nd). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (2nd) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (2nd) was dismissed by the court.

  • Kara Meagan Kennedy was found guilty of Vehicle Operator Flee/Elude Officer, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(3).
  • Kara Meagan Kennedy was found guilty of OWI (2nd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case called at 3:09pm [mo]
Defendant Kara Meagan Kennedy in court with Attorney Nicole Nannette Schrier.   ADA Brookellen Teuber appears for the State of Wisconsin.

Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of "No Contest" entered on Counts #1 and #2; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; the Court accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Count #3.

Sentencing arguments given by ADA Teuber
Sentencing arguments given by Atty. Schrier
Statement made by Ms. Kennedy

On Count #1, the Court withholds sentence, and places Defendant on Probation for 2 years, with conditions:
--to undergo any assessment, treatment or therapy as deemed appropriate by the Agent
--maintain absolute sobriety
--no presence in bars, taverns, or liquor stores at the discretion of the agent
--no operation of a motor vehicle without valid Driver's License and Agent's Approval
--to pay costs of $268 plus the $250 DNA surcharge
--submit DNA sample upon demand by designee/ Sheriff

The Court orders outright: operating privileges revoked for 6 months

The Court advises Mr. Kennedy she has the right to request expungement of the DNA sample 

On Count #2, the Court sentences the Defendant: 

--To serve  45 days  in the Jefferson County Jail, with Huber privileges to include for childcare purposes; to commence June 26, 2015 at 7:00pm
--Days credit for time already served: 3 days
--To pay fine of $350+ costs= $1379 plus $56.74 in blood testing costs to Jefferson County Sheriff's Dept.= $1435.74 plus the Court appointed attorney fees, to be paid in $100 per month installments, commencing on September 1, 2015 and on the first day of each month thereafter until paid in full; non-payment will result in 20 days in jail with Huber privileges, consecutive
--Revocation of drivers license for 14 months
--County alcohol and drug assessment ordered
--Victim impact panel attendance
--Ignition Interlock Device required on any vehicle driven by the Defendant for a 14 month period  
--6 demerit points assessed

The Court orders that the cash bail posted in this file be applied to the cost, fees and assessments.
